summary: The document is a Receivables Purchase Agreement dated 11 November 2025, involving PayPal (Europe) S.À R.L. et Cie, S.C.A. as the Seller and ALPS 2.0 Partners S.À R.L. as the Purchaser, with BNY Mellon Corporate Trustee Services Limited acting as the Security Agent. The agreement outlines the terms for the sale and purchase of receivables, including conditions precedent, representations, warranties, and various obligations of the parties involved. It also addresses confidentiality, data protection, governing law, and jurisdiction, among other provisions.
